[2] Select agent designation - request for comments
Date: Thu 16 Jul 2015
Source: The Federal Register [edited]
https://www.federalregister.gov/articles/2015/07/16/2015-17435/possession-use-and-transfer-of-select-agents-and-toxins-addition-of-certain-influenza-virus-strains


Possession, Use, and Transfer of Select Agents and Toxins; Addition of Certain Influenza Virus Strains to the List of Select Agents and Toxins
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Action
------
Notice Of Proposed Rulemaking And Request For Comments.

Summary
---------
The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) within the [US] Department of Health and Human Services (HHS) is proposing to add certain influenza virus strains to the list of HHS select agents and toxins. Specifically, we are proposing to add the influenza viruses that contain the hemagglutinin (HA) from the Goose Guangdong/1/96 lineage (the influenza viruses that contain the hemagglutinin (HA) from the A/Gs/Gd/1/96 lineage), including wild-type viruses, as a non-Tier 1 select agent. We are also proposing to add any influenza viruses that contain the HA from the A/Gs/Gd/1/96 lineage that were made transmissible among mammals by respiratory droplets in a laboratory as a Tier 1 select agent. We have determined that these influenza viruses have the potential to pose a severe threat to public health and safety.

Unified agenda
--------------
Possession, Use, and Transfer of Select Agents and Toxins: Addition of HPAI H5N1 Influenza Strains to the List of HHS Select Agents

